    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Acomastylis humilis are diarrhea and fever. Acomastylis humilis has been used to treat inflammation, with studies showing it reduces swelling and pain in patients with rheumatism. The plant is also effective in treating respiratory issues, such as bronchitis, with its expectorant properties helping to clear mucus from the lungs. Additionally, Acomastylis humilis has been used to treat gastrointestinal issues, including constipation, by regulating bowel movements. Furthermore, its antimicrobial properties also make it effective in treating skin infections, such as eczema.",
