    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Acomastylis humilis are its anti-inflammatory activity, which is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins, compounds that inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines. Antimicrobial activity, another key property of this plant, is mediated by volatile oils and phenolic acids, which have been shown to exhibit broad-spectrum activity against bacteria, fungi, and viruses. The plant's antioxidant properties are largely due to the presence of flavonoids, which scavenge free radicals and protect cells from oxidative damage. Acomastylis humilis also exhibits wound-healing activity, which is facilitated by the presence of saponins that enhance tissue repair and reduce inflammation. Its immunomodulatory activity, which is mediated by bioactive compounds such as phenolic acids and volatile oils, helps to regulate the immune response and prevent infection.",
