    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Acomastylis humilis are flavonoids, tannins, and phenolic acids, which have been proven to possess antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties. Flavonoids, in particular, have been found to exhibit anti-inflammatory activity by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines, while tannins have been shown to have antimicrobial properties against a range of microorganisms. Phenolic acids, such as caffeic and ferulic acid, have been found to have antioxidant activity, scavenging free radicals and protecting against oxidative stress. Additionally, Acomastylis humilis contains sesquiterpenes, such as guaiane and humilin, which have been reported to have antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory activity. The combination of these constituents may contribute to the plant's traditional use in treating various health conditions, including wound healing, fever reduction, and antimicrobial infections.",
