    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Acomastylis humilis are tincture made by soaking the roots in a solvent such as ethanol to extract its bioactive compounds, tea prepared by steeping the leaves in hot water to release its volatile oils, infusion where the leaves are steeped in cold water to preserve its delicate constituents, salve prepared by infusing the roots in a carrier oil to create a topical ointment, and decoction where the roots are boiled in water to extract its alkaloids and glycosides which are known for their medicinal properties. The tincture is used to treat digestive issues due to its antispasmodic properties. The tea is used for its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory effects. The infusion is used to treat respiratory issues due to its expectorant properties. The salve and decoction are used to treat skin issues and wounds due to their antimicrobial properties.",
